subSubSection.paragraph:
Tentacular cirri long, variably twisted, longest ones reaching chaetiger 4 (right) or 6 (left) (reaching chaetiger 5 in syntypes of
H. margaritae
). Lateral cushions slightly projected, surface entire in first three and last three chaetigers, other ones divided into anterior and posterior sections.

Posterior region tapered into a blunt cone; pygidium subspherical, surface granulate, anus projected ( Fig. 39C ), with 7 round, blunt papillae, four lateral, three dorsal ( 5-7 in syntypes of
H. margaritae
).

